text:
javascript click() fails to activate links. In the following document, clicking on the first link should display an alert,
followed by navigation to the second link. The alert appears but the second
link is not activated. It works fine in both IE and Opera, but fails under
Mozilla 1.0 too.

<HTML>
<BODY>
<SCRIPT>
function doit()
{
  alert("Doing it");
  lk = document.getElementsByName("thelink");
  lk.item(0).click();
}
</SCRIPT>

<A href="javascript:doit()">Do it</A>
<BR><BR>
<A name="thelink" href="test2.html">The Link</A>

</BODY>
</HTML>
